casebody.data:
STATE of Iowa, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Terry Thomas BRAGG, Defendant-Appellant. No. 18-1543 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed June 5, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION

See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

Terry Bragg appeals the district court's decision to require he serve the sentence imposed in this case consecutive to his sentence in another case asserting the court considered an impermissible sentencing factor and therefore abused its discretion. AFFIRMED.

AFFIRMED.
